text: Calabarzon is an administrative region in the Philippines. It is also known as Southern Tagalog Mainland or Region IV-A, It is on Luzon island. The capital is Calamba City and the administrative center is Lucena City. The region has five provinces: Cavite, Laguna, Batangas, Rizal, and Quezon. There is also one independent city, Lucena. ==Images== ==References==
